<h1>Contexts</h1>
<h2>Definition</h2>
	<p>The <span class="keyword">Context</span> is a centralizing, federative P&amp;O object linking 
		together the <span class="keyword">Project</span>, <span class="keyword">Role</span> and 
	<span class="keyword">Organization</span>.</p>
<h2>Use</h2>
<table cellSpacing="0" width="100%" border="0" valign="top" id="table1">
	<tr>
		<td>
		<div style="border-style: inset; border-width: 3px; padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px">
			<img src="images/helpContexts.png" width="342" height="258"></div>
		</td>
		<td><p>A
		<span class="keyword">Context</span> is assigned to
		<span class="keyword">Persons</span>, and a Person may have several 
		contexts.<br>
		When logging in VPLM, a person has to choose one of his context as the 
		current one, because :<ul>
			<li>this sets some contextual information (current organization &amp; 
			project) that are used to set ownership of objects created during 
			this VPLM session<br>
&nbsp;</li>
			<li>this may be used to configure access to object attributes in 
			GUI, through Masks</li>
			</ul>
			</td>
	</tr>
</table>
